# This conference will build on the work of earlier Bitcoin development conferences, including the online On-Chain Scaling conferences and Bitcoin Unlimited’s Satoshi’s Vision conference, and will be extended to roughly 2-4 times the size (~50-100 attendees) of the latter as a two-day, rather than a one-day, event.
# Provide a platform for diverse technical topics and approaches to future development of Bitcoin.
# Intend to issue an open &quot;call for proposals&quot; to allot a portion of the sp
# eaking slots.
# Funding to pay expenses for key-note speakers/attendees. Partial expenses may be offered on a case-by-case basis.
# Reaffirmation of Bitcoin as a peer-to-peer sound money, along with other potential use cases.
# Make the case for multiple implementations, i.e. decentralized development, resolving the last major centralizing force within the Bitcoin ecosystem.
# Presentations: Selected items drawn from the roadmaps of [https://bitco.in/forum/threads/bitcoin-unlimited-proposed-development-roadmap.1401/ Bitcoin Unlimited], [https://bitcoinclassic.com/roadmap.html Bitcoin Classic], [https://github.com/btcsuite/btcd BTCD], and [https://bitcoin.org/en/bitcoin-core/capacity-increases Bitcoin Core], and any others as appropriate.
